constructor.details: Constructor which deploys the proxy contract. The proxy contract stores all state for the AccountRegistry contract system

params.initialBehaviourAddress: - address of the behaviour contract to be linked to be initialised when the proxy is deployed
params.trustedGSNSignerAddress: - address that is being trusted to produce signatures to approve relayed GSN calls

getImplementation().details: Get the current behaviour contract address
getImplementation().return: implementation - address of the behaviour contract

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeAccountRegistry(address).details: Upgrade the account registry to a new behaviour implementation

params.newBehaviourAddress: - address of the behaviour contract to be upgraded to
